174
00:10:30,130 --> 00:10:31,839
Yes, I am.

175
00:10:31,965 --> 00:10:33,799
We'll find a treatment.

176
00:10:34,342 --> 00:10:37,261
I don't want to live like this.

177
00:10:38,555 --> 00:10:41,890
Please, I'm begging you.

178
00:10:43,184 --> 00:10:44,476
Kill me.

179
00:10:49,941 --> 00:10:51,191
He says no more tests.

180
00:10:51,359 --> 00:10:53,360
He wants to die and he wants us
to help him do it.

181
00:10:53,486 --> 00:10:56,905
And I wanna play a little game I like
to call Block My Spike with Misty May.

182
00:10:57,032 --> 00:10:59,313
He's thought this through.
It's not an impulsive decision.

183
00:10:59,409 --> 00:11:01,201
Neither is mine.
He's depressed.

184
00:11:01,328 --> 00:11:02,929
He'll feel much better
after we cure him.

185
00:11:03,038 --> 00:11:04,538
He's seen all the tests
we've seen.

186
00:11:04,664 --> 00:11:06,582
Even if we figure out
what's causing the lung damage,

187
00:11:06,708 --> 00:11:07,833
it's too late to reverse it.

188
00:11:07,959 --> 00:11:09,879
You can't know that
without knowing what's wrong.

189
00:11:09,919 --> 00:11:11,086
It's his call.

190
00:11:11,212 --> 00:11:12,212
So what do we do?

191
00:11:12,339 --> 00:11:14,298
Do we just put a plastic bag
over his head and get it over with?

192
00:11:14,424 --> 00:11:17,259
No, we give him
a syringe full of morphine.

193
00:11:19,596 --> 00:11:22,097
