has done it.

194
00:11:22,223 --> 00:11:23,766
They don't want to,
they don't like to,

195
00:11:23,892 --> 00:11:26,310
- but that's the way it is.
- I haven't. I won't.

196
00:11:26,436 --> 00:11:27,227
I couldn't do it either.

197
00:11:27,354 --> 00:11:29,396
You just said we should
respect his decision.

198
00:11:29,522 --> 00:11:31,982
Respect it doesn't necessarily
mean we honor it.

199
00:11:32,108 --> 00:11:34,568
Right. It just means
we talk about it.

200
00:11:34,944 --> 00:11:38,364
At some point, "do no harm" has to mean
allowing nature to take its course,

201
00:11:38,490 --> 00:11:40,157
not stubbornly
standing in the way of it.

202
00:11:40,283 --> 00:11:43,452
Sticking a metal syringe
into a plastic IV line and pumping in

203
00:11:43,578 --> 00:11:46,747
a lethal dose of morphine is not
letting nature take its course,

204
00:11:46,873 --> 00:11:48,123
not according to
the State of New Jersey.

205
00:11:48,249 --> 00:11:51,126
So it's better we allow him
to slowly suffocate in his own plasma?

206
00:11:51,252 --> 00:11:53,128
Whose side are you on, Senator?

207
00:11:53,254 --> 00:11:56,340
First respect his wishes, then invade
Iraq, then get the troops home.

208
00:11:56,466 --> 00:11:58,384
- Make up your mind.
- Wow.

209
00:11:59,177 --> 00:12:01,220
There's certainly a lot of interesting
things to consider.

210
00:12:01,346 --> 00:12:03,931
The stress EKG
rules out the heart,

211
00:12:04,057 --> 00:12:05,682
which means something's
gotta be attacking his lungs.

212
00:12:05,809 --> 00:12:09,144
Could be mycoplasma
or Strep pneumo, which probably means

213
00:12:09,270 --> 00:12:11,688
it's too late
to do anything about it.

214
00:12:11,815 --> 00:12:13,565
We could try levofloxacin.

215
00:12:13,691 --> 00:12:15,734
Coming up with a new treatment
isn't gonna do us any good

216
00:12:15,860 --> 00:12:18,153
unless we convince him
it's worth trying.

217
00:12:18,279 --> 00:12:22,199
Come on. He's old
and sick and tiny.

218
00:12:22,325 --> 00:12:24,201
And we can do
whatever we want to him.

219
00:12:34,254 --> 00:12:35,754
What happened?

220
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:37,214
I don't know.

221
00:12:37,340 --> 00:12:38,382
He must have fallen out of bed

222
00:12:38,508 --> 00:12:41,593
and got the nasal cannula
wrapped around his neck somehow.

223
00:12:41,719 --> 00:12:43,637
Ezra, what are you doing?

224
00:12:43,763 --> 00:12:48,267
I don't want to live hooked to machines,
too weak to wipe my own ass.

225
00:12:48,393 --> 00:12:49,913
Why would you want to
wipe your own ass

226
00:12:49,978 --> 00:12:51,437
when you could have someone
do it for you?

227
00:12:51,563 --> 00:12:53,105
You're wasting your time.

228
00:12:53,231 --> 00:12:55,311
There must be other patients
you could actually help.

229
00:12:55,358 --> 00:12:59,319
All services rendered
on a first come, first served basis.

230
00:12:59,487 --> 00:13:02,322
I won't consent
to any more tests.

231
00:13:03,366 --> 00:13:06,368
And if anyone tries to
so much as touch me,

232
00:13:07,162 --> 00:13:09,288
I'll press charges for assault.

233
00:13:11,458 --> 00:13:12,833
You heard the man.

234
00:13:12,959 --> 00:13:16,670
He wants everyone to leave him alone.
Why don't you go first?

235
00:13:18,006 --> 00:13:19,298
Get out!

236
00:13:28,349 --> 00:13:31,101
You came to me.
I didn't come to you.

237
00:13:31,352 --> 00:13:33,061
I figured you'd have the guts

238
00:13:33,188 --> 00:13:36,106
to do what had to be done
if it came to that.

239
00:13:36,983 --> 00:13:40,277
We're nowhere near that.
It's time to test your lungs.

240
00:13:45,074 --> 00:13:46,408
Breathe!

241
00:13:46,534 --> 00:13:47,993
You're gonna have to
exhale sometime.

242
00:13:48,119 --> 00:13:49,077
Stop!

243
00:13:49,204 --> 00:13:50,329
House, you're hurting him.

244
00:13:50,455 --> 00:13:51,538
You're hurting me.

